        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on</span><span class=\"english\"> “</span><span class=\"english\">Manners and Etiquette</span><span class=\"english\">” </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences. </span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Manners and Etiquette</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Manners and etiquette are vital elements of civilized behaviour that shape how people live together in society. Manners are universal principles of politeness, such as respect, gratitude, kindness, and honesty. For example, using words like “please,” “thank you,” and “sorry” reflects good manners everywhere. In contrast, etiquette refers to specific social rules and customs that vary across cultures and situations. For instance, bowing is proper etiquette in Japan, while shaking hands is common in Western countries. Thus, manners are general and timeless, while etiquette depends on culture and tradition. Their importance lies in creating harmony, reducing conflicts, and showing consideration for others. Good manners make daily life smooth, while proper etiquette helps people adjust in different societies. They are also necessary in professional life, where behaviour often determines success. A person who practices both manners and etiquette not only earns respect but also strengthens social unity and cooperation.</span><span> </span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Marks ----------------------------------------------09 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For </span><span class=\"english\">Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Manners and Etiquette</span><span class=\"english\">) -------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -----------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Manners and etiquette are vital elements of civilized behaviour that shape how people live together in society. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Manners and Etiquette in Civilized Behaviour</span><span class=\"english\">) (Any 6 Points) </span><span class=\"english\">----</span><span class=\"english\">06 Marks  </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Manners are universal principles of politeness like respect, gratitude, kindness, and honesty.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Etiquette refers to specific social rules and customs varying across cultures and situations.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">•</span><span class=\"english\"> Manners are general and timeless, while etiquette depends on culture and tradition.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Manners create harmony, reduce conflicts, and show consideration for others.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Good manners make daily life smooth, while proper etiquette helps adjust in different societies.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Practice of both manners and etiquette </span><span class=\"english\">are also necessary in professional life, where behaviour often determines success.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion </span><span class=\"english\">-----------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">In conclusion, a person who practices both manners and etiquette not only earns respect but also strengthens social unity and cooperation.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. (Comment: Write within single/one para). </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4. For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark. (comment: Write the Title /</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Manners and Etiquette)</span></p><p></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Explain the proverb:</span><span class=\"english\"> “Cut your coat according to cloth”</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>5</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">This proverb encourages living within your means and avoiding excessive spending. It suggests that one should not exceed their resources and should be content with what they have. For instance, </span><span class=\"english\">someone on a tight budget should avoid extravagant purchases and instead focus on essentials. Living frugally and managing your resources wisely is crucial to maintaining financial stability. The message is to be mindful of financial limits and avoid wastefulness. It also teaches that by staying within one's means, a person can ensure security and avoid unnecessary stress caused by overspending.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Mark Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A) Theme of The Proverb-----------------01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">• The proverb illustrates living within your means and avoiding excessive spending.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">B) Context of The Proverb (</span><span class=\"english\">Cut your coat according to cloth</span><span class=\"english\">) ( 03 points) -----03 marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Encourages contentment with limited resources.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Stresses the importance of managing resources wisely for financial stability.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Stresses the need to be mindful of financial limits and avoid wastefulness.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C)Conclusion ------------------------------------------- 01 mark                                                                     </span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">Ultimately, this proverb </span><span class=\"english\">teaches that by staying within one's means, a person can ensure security and avoid unnecessary stress caused by overspending.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">[N.B. For every 03 spelling or grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.]</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Make meaningful sentences with the following words.</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>5</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Attitude, Misuse, Practitioner, Bystander, Crept</span></p>",
