        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Attitude (Noun) = His positive </span><span class=\"english\">attitude</span><span class=\"english\"> towards challenges inspired the people around him.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Misuse (Noun) = The </span><span class=\"english\">misuse</span><span class=\"english\"> of mobile phones in class can cause distractions.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Misuse (Verb) = Many people </span><span class=\"english\">misuse</span><span class=\"english\"> freedom of speech on social media.</span><span class=\"english\"> [Students can use it both as Noun and Verb]</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Practitioner (Noun) = A doctor is a medical </span><span class=\"english\">practitioner</span><span class=\"english\"> who helps people stay healthy.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Bystander (Noun) = The incident took place in front of horrified </span><span class=\"english\">bystanders</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Crept (Verb) = The cat </span><span class=\"english\">crept</span><span class=\"english\"> silently toward the bird to avoid being noticed.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><a></a><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(i)</span><span class=\"english\"> Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii)</span><span class=\"english\"> For </span><span class=\"english\">02</span><span class=\"english\"> spelling mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted, for </span><span class=\"english\">01 spelling</span><span class=\"english\"> mistake, </span><span class=\"english\">0.5 marks</span><span class=\"english\"> will be deducted from that very sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">(iv)</span><span class=\"english\"> For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a </span><span class=\"english\">suffix or prefix</span><span class=\"english\">, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the </span><span class=\"english\">subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number</span><span class=\"english\">, etc.)</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎Comment: </span><span class=\"english\">Use the given word without changing its parts of speech</span><span class=\"english\">.</span></p>"
